[3] Suspected, research, funding

8 Oct 2015 Mali: President Keita declares Mali as Ebola free
http://www.voicechronicle.com/1546-30-president-keita-declares-mali-ebola-free/

8 Oct 2015 Nigeria: FG dispatches medical team as Ebola scare hits Calabar
http://www.vanguardngr.com/2015/10/fg-dispatches-medical-team-as-ebola-scare-hits-calabar/
[The Federal Government has dispatched a medical team to Calabar, Cross River state to ascertain the suspected Ebola scare. The accident and emergency ward of the University of Calabar Teaching Hospital has been shut down following an Ebola virus scare. However, the Federal Ministry of Health has ruled out the case [as] Ebola, saying that it suspected that the patient could have died of haemorrhagic fever.]

BUT SEE FOLLOW-UP:
9 Oct 2015 WHO: Nigerian at centre of Ebola scare did not have the virus
http://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/world/nigerian-at-centre-of-ebo/2181284.html

["The dead person tested negative for Ebola. So this person is not going to be the source of an Ebola event," [WHO spokesperson] Hartl wrote. "A laboratory investigation showed the dead person did not have Ebola or Lassa fever," Hartl said.

It is not clear which hemorrhagic fever virus is suspect at this time. A number of other viruses endemic to the region besides Lassa present with hemorrhagic fever, including those causing Marburg, CCHF (Crimean-Congo hemorrhagic fever), Rift Valley fever and yellow fever. It is important to know which one, because if it was yellow fever, vaccination is urgently needed. Any further information would be greatly appreciated; Nigeria has the diagnostic capability. - Mod.LK/JW]

Vaccines, drugs, research
-----------------------
8 Oct 2015: Liberia: Crusaders for Peace, PREVAIL set rules for Ebola research
http://allafrica.com/stories/201510090907.html
[On Wed 7 Oct 2015, The Liberia Crusaders for Peace (LCP) and the Partnership for Research on Ebola virus disease in Liberia (PREVAIL) set clear guidelines for enrollment in the on-going medical research on Ebola survivors and close contacts.]

9 Oct 2015: Antiviral compound effectively treated Ebola in monkeys
http://www.upi.com/Health_News/2015/10/09/Antiviral-compound-effectively-treated-Ebola-in-monkeys/7091444413568/?spt=sec&or=hn
[In a clinical trial of the compound GS-5374, which is currently being conducted by Gilead Sciences, it blocks the ability of the Ebola virus to replicate in the body, successfully preventing rhesus monkeys from succumbing to Ebola virus disease (EVD). Gilead Sciences worked with the United States Army Medical Research Institute of Infectious Diseases (USAMRIID) to develop the vaccine. GS-5374 was also effective in the lab against Middle East respiratory syndrome (MERS), Marburg virus, and several variants of Ebola virus, including the strain responsible for the current outbreak in West Africa. The compound works by blocking the viral RNA replication process.]

11 Oct 2015 China-made Ebola Vaccine, Clinical Trial Initiation, Sierra Leone
http://www.chinanews.com/gj/2015/10-11/7563531.shtml
[China's 1st self-developed recombinant Ebola vaccine formally launched Phase II clinical trials in Sierra Leone. This is the 1st time that a self-produced Ebola vaccine from China has received approval for clinical trials abroad. This vaccine was developed by the Innovation Team under Director Chen Wei of the Bioengineering Research Center at the China PLA Academy of Military Medical Sciences. Phase I clinical trials were completed at China Taizhou Medical City and Zhejiang University on Chinese and on Africans residing in China, proving the safety and efficacy of the vaccine. The clinical trial results were published in the UK's The Lancet."

Abstract in Lancet:
http://www.thelancet.com/journals/lancet/article/PIIS0140-6736(15)60553-0/abstract]

